      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Westwood ¶ River Forth ¶ Tasmania ¶ 15th Dec. 1894 ¶ Dear Baron Von Mueller,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.12.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Smith</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">James Smith (1827-1897).</p>
               </note>Westwood</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">River Forth</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Tasmania</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15th Dec. 1894</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron Von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sending by this post a number of botanical Specimens from Mount Bischoff.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Tas.</p>
               </note> Those that are loose (not tied with string) are from within fifty feet (as to level) of the apex of the mountain; those that are bound with string are from a lower level where the soil is of better quality though about a hundred feet higher than the adjacent table land and are all from the south side of the mountain which is exposed to the coldest winds. I have included a leaf of blandfordia<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>i.e. the genus <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Blandfordia">Blandfordia</name>
                     </seg>.</p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but something, I think goats, seem to have been cropping this plant on the mountain.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please inform me as to the names of those specimens I have numbered 1, 2 and 3 and of the specimens with the red and blue berries.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">with kind regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours truly,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Smith</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. No. 1, which seems to me to be a variety of native laurel, has when in a state of rottenness in scrubs, a very offensive smell.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">J.S.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Blandfordia">Blandfordia</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
